Date: Tue, 31 Aug 1999 11:29:12 +0200
From: "Heikki Henttonen" <heikki.henttonen@metla.fi>
Re:
> Hemorrhagic fever with renal syndrome (HFRS) large-scale outbreaks are
> periodically (once every 3-4 years) registered in Bashkortostan
(Bashkiria,
> Bashkirskaya). Serotyping confirms that the agent is Hantaan virus.
The statement above is wrong. Maybe Alex has confused hanta and Hantaan
(which is not so rare). Bashkirian HFRS is caused by Puumala hantavirus,
carried by the bank vole _Clethrionomys glareolus_. Maybe Prof. Tkachenko
could give more data.
Hantaan virus has not been found in Europe. Instead, two strains of Dobrava,
one in _Apodemus agrarius_, the other in _A. flavicollis_ [field mice, are
found in Europe. Dobrava belongs to the same murine clade of hantaviruses as
Seoul and Hantaan.
